âœ… 1. What display: none meant in your modal project

When .overlay or .modal had display: none, they were completely invisible.

They also did not occupy any space on the page.

So even though the elements were in the HTML, the browser behaved as if they were not there.

ğŸ” In your modal website:
Before clicking â€œOpen Modalâ€, the overlay + modal were not visible at all because of display: none.

âœ… 2. What happens when JS changes display: none â†’ display: block

The element becomes visible on the screen.

It is now rendered by the browser.

Only visibility is controlled.
(Nothing about position or layering.)

ğŸ” In your modal website:
When you clicked â€œOpen Modalâ€ â†’ JavaScript set:
overlay.style.display = 'block'
modal.style.display = 'block'
And they appeared.

âœ… 3. Why display:block did NOT push your page down

Normally block elements push other elements down.
But yours didnâ€™t â€” and that confused you.

Here is why:

âœ” Because your overlay and modal used position: fixed.

When an element has position: fixed:

It is removed from the normal flow.

It does not push any other element.

It floats on top of the screen.

It appears above the page even if it comes before or after other elements.

ğŸ” In your modal website:
Even though you set display:block, the overlay did not push your button down because it was position: fixed.

âœ… 4. Why we MUST use position: fixed for overlays

Overlays must:

cover the whole screen

not push anything

stay fixed even when scrolling

appear above the page

position: fixed allows all this.

ğŸ” In your modal website:
Your .overlay covered the entire screen and blocked the page behind it â€” because of position: fixed.

âœ… 5. Why the overlay did NOT cover the modal

You were confused why:

overlay becomes display:block

overlay comes up

modal also becomes block

but modal stays above the overlay (not behind it)

The reason is:

âœ” The modal had a higher z-index than the overlay.

Example you used (or similar):

.overlay { z-index: 1000; }
.modal { z-index: 2000; }


So even though:

overlay is block

overlay comes first in HTML

Modal still appears above overlay because of z-index.

ğŸ” In your modal website:
Modal popped up on top of the dark overlay because modalâ€™s z-index was higher.

âœ… 6. HTML order did NOT matter in your modal

You worried:

â€œWill overlay cover the modal because overlay comes before/after in HTML?â€

Answer: No.
When position and z-index are used, HTML order does not decide stacking.

ğŸ” In your modal website:
No matter where you write the overlay and modal in HTML, their z-index decides who sits on top.

âœ… 7. What you understood about display types (based on your learning flow)
âœ” display: none

Used to hide overlay & modal before clicking.

Made them behave like they donâ€™t exist.

âœ” display: block

Used to show them when needed.

Makes them visible.

But in your case, because of position: fixed, they didnâ€™t push the layout.

âœ” display: inline and display: inline-block

You understood these earlier for buttons, spans, etc.

display:inline â†’ sits alongside text.

display:block â†’ behaves like div (takes full width).

Used when you want inline things to behave like blocks.

These were useful for general layout but not directly involved in your modal mechanics.

âœ… 8. What you clearly understood about position (based on your project)
âœ” position: fixed

Used for overlay & modal:

sticks to screen

covers the whole viewport

stays on top

does NOT push anything

âœ” position: absolute

You understood:

positions relative to the nearest positioned parent

also removed from normal flow

but scrolls with page

Modal overlays usually do NOT use absolute because absolute scrolls with the page â€” not good for a popup.

ğŸ¯ FINAL QUICK REVISION (THE MOST IMPORTANT)
ğŸ”µ display controls: visible or invisible

none â†’ fully hidden

block â†’ visible

ğŸ”µ position controls: how the element sits

fixed â†’ floats above page, no pushing

absolute â†’ floats but scrolls with page

static â†’ normal flow

relative â†’ normal flow + move slightly

ğŸ”µ z-index controls: who is on top

Higher z-index = on top.

â­ SUPER-SHORT VERSION (for quick revision later)

display:none = hide modal + overlay

display:block = show them

position:fixed = float on top without pushing

overlay covers whole page because of fixed + top:0; left:0

